## read result files
files <- list.files("out/disease_each/", pattern = "md.rds") %>% paste0("out/disease_each/", .)

res <- c()
for(i in files){
  df <- read_rds(i)
  
  temp <- df$study %>% str_split("\\_", simplify = T)    
  if(ncol(temp) == 1){
    df$study2 <- temp[, 1]
  }else{
    df$study2 <- paste0(temp[, 1], " ", temp[, 2])
  }
  res <- rbind(res, df)
}
res$study2 <- res$study2 %>% str_replace(" $", "")
res$group <- factor(res$group, levels = c("Control", "Case"))
res$disease_label <- res$disease_label %>% str_wrap(width = 10)

keep1 <- res$disease_label %>% str_detect("^[ABC]")
keep2 <- res$disease_label %>% str_detect("^[DEFGHIJKLMNOP]")
keep3 <- res$disease_label %>% str_detect("^[QRSTUVWXYZ]")

p1 <- ggplot(res[keep1, ], aes(x = study2, y = count, fill = group)) +
  theme_bw() +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.8, outlier.size = -1) +  
  ylab("Microbial load") +
  theme(strip.text.x = element_text(size = 10)) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) +
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(colour = "black", size = 0.5)) +
  theme(strip.text.y = element_text(angle = 0)) +

  theme(legend.position = "none") +

Ordination of disease signatures

## read count data
files <- list.files("out/disease_each/", pattern = "count.rds") %>% paste0("out/disease_each/", .)

stat <- c()
for(i in files){
  temp.res <- read_rds(i)
  stat <- rbind(stat, temp.res)
}
stat$fdr <- p.adjust(stat$p, method = "fdr")
stat$dir <- stat$e > 0

## read microbiome data
files <- list.files("out/disease_each/", pattern = ".tsv") %>% paste0("out/disease_each/", .)
res <- c()
for(i in files){
  d <- read.delim(i, header = T, row.names = 1)
  temp <- d %>% dplyr::select(name, e, disease)
  res <- rbind(res, temp)
}

d <- res %>% spread(disease, e)
rownames(d) <- d$name
d <- d[, -1]

keep <- apply(is.na(d), 1, sum) < 5
d <- d[keep, ]

## calc distance matrics
cor <- (1 - cor(d, method = "spearman", use = "pairwise.complete.obs")) / 2

## PCoA
adonis.res <- adonis2(as.dist(cor) ~ stat$dir, permutations = 9999)
adonis.p <- adonis.res$`Pr(>F)`[1] %>% paste0("P = ", .)
cor.mds <- cmdscale(as.dist(cor))
df <- data.frame(disease = colnames(d), x = cor.mds[, 1], y = cor.mds[, 2])

df <- inner_join(df, stat[, c("disease", "dir", "fdr")], by = "disease")
df$label <- df$disease
df$label <- ifelse(df$fdr < 0.1, df$label, "")

p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = x, y = y, label = label, col = dir)) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank()) +
  xlab("PCoA 1") +
  ylab("PCoA 2") +  
  stat_ellipse(show.legend = F, alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6, shape = 21) +  
  geom_point(data = subset(df, fdr < 0.1), alpha = 0.6) +
  ggrepel::geom_text_repel(show.legend = F, size = 2.5, col = "black") +  
  scale_color_manual(values = c(dj[5], dj[1]), labels = c("Negatively-associated disease", "Positively-associated disease")) +
  annotate("text", x = -Inf, y = -Inf, label = adonis.p, vjust = -1, hjust = -0.5, size = 3) +
  scale_size(range = c(1, 6)) +
  theme(legend.text = element_text(size = 8)) +
  theme(legend.position = "right", legend.title = element_blank())
p
